 listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Disney acquisitions]]\n[[Category:The Walt Disney Company subsidiaries]]\n[[Category:2009 mergers and acquisitions]]\n", "name_user": "2605:a000:1100:87f4:6107:9715:dc2:36d8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eProductions)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marvel_Entertainment"}
{"title_page": "2020 in Somalia", "text_new": "{{Year in Somalia|2020}}\n\nEvents in the year '''2020 in [[Somalia]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[President of Somalia|President]]: [[Mohamed Abdullahi Mohamed]] (since 16 February 2017)\n*[[Prime Minister of Somalia|Prime Minister]]: [[Hassan Ali Khayre]] (since 1 March 2017)\n\n==Events==\n\n===Ongoing===\n*[[Somali Civil War (2009\u2013present)]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Somalia]]\n\n===January===\n* [[18 January]] &ndash; [[2020 Afgooye bombing]]\n\n===February===\n* [[19 February]] &ndash; [[El Salini attack]]\n\n===Scheduled===\n*[[2020 Somali parliamentary election]], the first [[elections in Somalia]] under a [[one man, one vote|one person, one vote]] system since the [[1969 Somali parliamentary election]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/feb/24/somalia-edges-closer-to-first-democratic-election-in-half-a-century|first=Moulid|last=Hujale|title=Somalia edges closer to first democratic election in half a century|newspaper=The Guardian|date=24 February 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n* 24 March &ndash; [[Mohamed Farah (footballer)|Mohamed Farah]], 59, footballer ([[Somalia national football team|national team]]), COVID-19<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tv360nigeria.com/african-football-legend-mohamed-farah-dies-from-covid-19/|first=Adesewa|last=Odusoga|title=African Football Legend Mohamed Farah Dies From COVID-19|publisher=TV 360 Nigeria|date=27 March 2020|access-date=10 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327170912/https://www.tv360nigeria.com/african-football-legend-mohamed-farah-dies-from-covid-19/|archive-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"abroad\">Died abroad</ref>\n* 1 April &ndash; [[Nur Hassan Hussein]], 83, politician, [[List of prime ministers of Somalia|Prime Minister]] (2007\u20132009), COVID-19<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.garoweonline.com/en/news/somalia/ex-somali-pm-dies-of-coronavirus-in-london|title=Ex-Somali PM dies of Coronavirus in London|work=Garowe Online|date=1 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"abroad\"/>\n* 7 April &ndash; [[Hudeydi]], 91, [[oud]] player, COVID-19<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.okayafrica.com/somali-musician-ismail-hussein-hudeydi-among-africans-die-from-coronavirus/|first=Rufaro|last=Samanga|title=Veteran Somali Musician Ahmed Ismail Hussein Has Died|work=Okey Africa|date=8 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"abroad\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 in Somaliland]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Africa topic|2020 in}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Somalia| ]]\n[[Category:2020s in Somalia]]\n[[Category:Years of the 21st century in Somalia]]\n[[Category:2020 in Africa|Somalia]]\n[[Category:2020 by country|Somalia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in Somalia|2020}}\n\nEvents in the year '''2020 in [[Somalia]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[President of Somalia|President]]: [[Mohamed Abdullahi Mohamed]] (since 16 February 2017)\n*[[Prime Minister of Somalia|Prime Minister]]: [[Hassan Ali Khayre]] (since 1 March 2017)\n\n==Events==\n\n===Ongoing===\n*[[Somali Civil War (2009\u2013present)]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Somalia]]\n\n===January===\n* [[18 January]] &ndash; [[2020 Afgooye bombing]]\n\n===February===\n* [[19 February]] &ndash; [[El Salini attack]]\n\n===Scheduled===\n*[[2020 Somali parliamentary election]], the first [[elections in Somalia]] under a [[one man, one vote|one person, one vote]] system since the [[1969 Somali parliamentary election]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/feb/24/somalia-edges-closer-to-first-democratic-election-in-half-a-century|first=Moulid|last=Hujale|title=Somalia edges closer to first democratic election in half a century|newspaper=The Guardian|date=24 February 2020|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n* 24 March &ndash; [[